# Product Overview — Financial Metrics Dashboard

## What it is
A financial monitoring dashboard giving an at-a-glance view of a
business's income, spending, and profitability over time.

## Who it's for
Someone checking business financial health at a glance — a business
owner, finance lead, or similar — not someone doing deep transaction-
level analysis. The current UI supports viewing only, not drilling in.

## Core features (as currently implemented)
- Four top-level KPI cards: Total Income, Total Outcome, Profit,
  Profit Margin
- Two monthly trend charts: Income vs. Outcome, and Profit Margin %
- Hover tooltips on chart data points (month, year, value)

## What it does NOT currently do
Despite backend support existing for all of the below, none of it is
exposed in the UI (see `current-status.md` for details):
- No filtering by date range, category, operation type, or B2B/B2C
- No sorting or drill-down into individual transactions
- No comparison between time periods, even though the backend has a
  dedicated `/api/metrics/comparison` endpoint for exactly this

## Data
All data is procedurally generated mock data (seeded, so it's
consistent across requests), not real financial records. There is no
database or persistence layer.